```javascript
// Create text index first
db.movies.createIndex({ "title": "text", "plot": "text" });

// Text search (requires text index)
db.movies.find({ $text: { $search: "godfather" } });

// Advanced text search with scoring
db.movies.find(
    { $text: { $search: "love story romance" } },
    { score: { $meta: "textScore" } }
).sort({ score: { $meta: "textScore" } });

// Text search with phrase and exclusion
db.movies.find({ 
    $text: { 
        $search: '"star wars" -prequel' 
    } 
});

// Regex search (no index required)
db.movies.find({
    "title": { $regex: "godfather", $options: "i" }
});

// Combined regex patterns
db.movies.find({
    $or: [
        { "title": { $regex: "star wars", $options: "i" } },
        { "title": { $regex: "star trek", $options: "i" } }
    ]
});
```

**Comparison: `$regex` vs `$text`**

| Feature | `$regex` | `$text` |
|---------|----------|--------|
| **Index Requirement** | Optional (2d, sparse) | Required (text index) |
| **Performance** | Slower on large datasets | Faster with proper indexing |
| **Language Support** | Basic pattern matching | Language-aware (stemming, stop words) |
| **Scoring** | No relevance scoring | Built-in relevance scoring |
| **Phrase Search** | Manual pattern construction | Native phrase support with quotes |
| **Case Sensitivity** | Manual with options | Automatically case-insensitive |
| **Fuzzy Matching** | No | Limited fuzzy capabilities |

**When to use:**
- **`$regex`**: Pattern matching, partial string searches, simple text filtering
- **`$text`**: Full-text search, relevance ranking, multi-language content

**GeoJSON Coordinate Order:**
In GeoJSON format, coordinates are always in **[longitude, latitude]** order:
- **Longitude**: East-West position (-180 to 180)
- **Latitude**: North-South position (-90 to 90)

```javascript
// Correct GeoJSON Point format
location: {
    type: "Point",
    coordinates: [-73.856077, 40.848447] // [longitude, latitude]
}

// Common coordinate examples
const coordinates = {
    "Times Square": [-73.9857, 40.7484],
    "Central Park": [-73.9654, 40.7829],
    "Brooklyn Bridge": [-73.9969, 40.7061],
    "Statue of Liberty": [-74.0445, 40.6892]
};

// $near - Find closest points (sorted by distance)
db.theaters.find({
    "location.geo": {
        $near: {
            $geometry: {
                type: "Point",
                coordinates: [-73.9857, 40.7484] // Times Square [lng, lat]
            },
            $maxDistance: 1000 // 1km radius
        }
    }
});

// $geoWithin - Find points within area (unsorted)
db.theaters.find({
    "location.geo": {
        $geoWithin: {
            $centerSphere: [
                [-73.9857, 40.7484], // Center point [lng, lat]
                5 / 3963.2 // 5 miles in radians
            ]
        }
    }
});

// $geoIntersects - Find geometries that intersect
db.theaters.find({
    "location.geo": {
        $geoIntersects: {
            $geometry: {
                type: "Polygon",
                coordinates: [[
                    [-74.0, 40.7],  // [lng, lat] - SW corner
                    [-73.9, 40.7],  // [lng, lat] - SE corner  
                    [-73.9, 40.8],  // [lng, lat] - NE corner
                    [-74.0, 40.8],  // [lng, lat] - NW corner
                    [-74.0, 40.7]   // [lng, lat] - Close polygon
                ]]
            }
        }
    }
});
```

**Memory Tips:**
- Think "**X, Y**" where X=longitude (horizontal), Y=latitude (vertical)
- Longitude comes first (like reading left to right)
- NYC example: [-73.xx, 40.xx] - negative longitude (west), positive latitude (north)

```javascript
// Find theaters and nearby restaurants (hypothetical collections)
db.theaters.aggregate([
    {
        $match: { "location.state": "NY" } // Filter theaters in NY
    },
