**Storage Engine Comparison:**

| Feature | WiredTiger | MMAPv1 | In-Memory |
|---------|------------|--------|-----------|
| **Status** | Default & Recommended | Deprecated | Enterprise Only |
| **Concurrency** | Document-level locking | Collection-level locking | Document-level locking |
| **Compression** | Yes (Snappy, zlib, zstd) | No | N/A |
| **Caching** | Configurable internal cache | Relies on OS cache | All data in RAM |
| **Persistence** | Persistent | Persistent | Non-persistent |
| **Performance** | High | Moderate | Ultra-high |
| **Memory Usage** | Efficient | Higher | RAM-dependent |
| **Write Performance** | Excellent | Good | Excellent |
| **Read Performance** | Excellent | Good | Ultra-fast |

**1. WiredTiger (Default & Recommended):**

```javascript
// WiredTiger advantages demonstration

// Document-level concurrency - multiple writers can work simultaneously
const Promise = require('bluebird');

// This would cause blocking in MMAPv1 but works efficiently in WiredTiger
const concurrentWrites = async () => {
    const writes = [];

    for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
        writes.push(
            User.create({
                name: `User ${i}`,
                email: `user${i}@example.com`,
                data: generateLargeData()
            })
        );
    }

    // All writes can proceed simultaneously
    const results = await Promise.all(writes);
    console.log(`Created ${results.length} users concurrently`);
};

// Compression benefits
const compressionExample = {
    // Original document size: ~1MB
    userData: {
        profile: {
            description: "A".repeat(100000), // Large text field
            preferences: {
                notifications: true,
                privacy: "private",
                themes: ["dark", "light", "auto"]
            }
        },
        activity: Array(1000).fill().map((_, i) => ({
            timestamp: new Date(),
            action: `action_${i}`,
            data: `data_${i}".repeat(100)`
        }))
    }
    // With Snappy compression: ~300KB storage
    // With zlib compression: ~200KB storage (slower but better ratio)
};
```

**WiredTiger Features:**
- **Document-Level Concurrency**: Multiple clients can modify different documents simultaneously
- **Compression**: Reduces storage space by 50-80% with minimal performance impact
- **Caching**: Configurable internal cache (default: 50% of RAM - 1GB)
- **Checkpointing**: Periodic snapshots ensure data durability
- **Journal**: Write-ahead logging for crash recovery

**2. MMAPv1 (Deprecated):**

| Limitation | Impact | WiredTiger Solution |
|------------|--------|-----------------|
| **Collection-level locking** | One writer per collection | Document-level locking |
| **No compression** | Larger storage requirements | Built-in compression |
| **Memory mapping** | Relies on OS virtual memory | Dedicated cache management |
| **Power of 2 allocation** | Space wastage | Efficient space allocation |

**3. In-Memory Storage Engine:**

```javascript
